oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Greenback Supply Co
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Edwin Best
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Greenback (Tenn.); Greenback Supply Co.; Business;
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This building stood for 14 years, and during that time it housed five business firms. Stone building with four windows on second floor, four windows and two doors on ground floor. Several people, men and women, pose for the picture. On the front of the building are signs for Studebaker Wagons and Greenback Supply Co.: For Hardware Vehicles Farm Implements Etc.
